The paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on distributional reinforcement learning and gradient temporal-difference learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with policy evaluation and control, which are topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses convergence analysis, which is related to optimization and falls under cs.LO (Optimization and Control).
